Y! The TAs can be real sticklers about the formatting of your code and the actual files you submit. For example, forgetting to rename a folder before zipping it leads to a point deduction even if you renamed it after zipping.\nMidterm (25%) - 10 definitions and 40 multiple choice questions. Its a cakewalk if you get your hands on past exams. The mean was about a 78 in my semester.\nFinal (35%) - It mirrors the midterm for the most part, but it also includes a section where you debug code by hand. Pay attention to the code that Cannon goes over in class, as he makes it clear that anything hes covered is fair game.	9	1	515	7002
